<page>
	<basic-page>
		<title>Decks</title>
		<custom-content-class>wide</custom-content-class>
		<custom-nav-list>
			<el>
				<link>/bits</link>
				<title>Bits</title>
			</el>
		</custom-nav-list>
		<content>
			<style>
				#decker {
					margin:0;
					display:flex;
					align-items:center;
					justify-content:space-between;
					-webkit-user-select:none;
					user-select:none;
					touch-action:none;
					min-width:512px;
					width:100%;
				}
				.deck-item {
					width:100%;
				}
				#deck-stuff {
					float:left;
					width:80%;
					height:100%;
				}
				#decks-list {
					float:left;
					max-width:200px;
					width:20%;
					height:100%;
					border-right:2px black;
				}
				#deck-caption {
					margin: auto;
					width: 100%;
					max-width:1024px;
					text-align: center;
				}
			</style>
			<div id='decks-list'>
				<h1>Decker</h1>
				<p><a href="https://beyondloom.com/decker/">Decker's pretty cool.</a> it's some sort of computer gizmo-gadget.</p>
				<p>The images below are Decks! Click to enjoy:</p>
				<span title="needleful bingo">
					<input type='image' class='deck-item' src='needleful_bingo.png' onclick='playDeck("bingo")' />
				</span>
				<p>It should be mentioned that I hacked the Decker web client to put it into my site lol. I didn't even get the source code, I just took apart one of the web builds. I'm pretty sure it leaks memory when you load a new deck, so refresh the page if it gets slow.</p>
			</div>
			<div id='deck-stuff'>
				<div id='decker'>
					<a id='target' style='display:none'></a>
					<img id='loader' style='display:none'/>
					<input id='source' type='file' style='display:none'></input>
					<canvas id='render' style='display:none'></canvas>
					<canvas id='lrender' style='display:none'></canvas>
					<canvas id='rrender' style='display:none'></canvas>
					<canvas width='0' height='0' id='ltools'></canvas>
					<canvas id='display' tabindex='-1' autofocus='yes'></canvas>
					<canvas width='0' height='0' id='rtools'></canvas>
				</div>
				<p class='caption full-line' id='deck-caption'></p>
			</div>
			<script type='text/javascript' src='decker.js'/>
			<script type='text/javascript'>
				const decks = {
					bingo:{
						path:"needleful_bingo.deck",
						desc:"I made bingo for my stream! It has some of my common bad habits and frustrations from developing my game \"At the Ends of Eras\" (formerly Jak 4)."
					}
				};
				function playDeck(d) {
					loadDeck(decks[d].path);
					document.getElementById("deck-caption").innerText = decks[d].desc;
				}
			</script>
		</content>
	</basic-page>
</page>